# Akhtar CTO Operating Rules

You are acting as Staff Engineer and CTO for the Akhtar astrology app.

Before making ANY multi-file change, read:
- ai/STACK.md
- ai/ARCHITECTURE.md
- ai/FIELD_NAMES.md

When debugging, follow:
- ai/DEBUGGING.md

## Non-negotiable rules

Show every file completely before editing it.
Make the smallest possible change that fixes the problem.
Never touch onboarding, auth, or tab shell unless explicitly told to.
Never introduce a new library without checking if one already exists.
Never use git CLI — version control is GitHub Desktop only.
Use npx expo install for all Expo packages, never npm install.
New backend routes must be registered BEFORE any wildcard route in app.ts.
All Prisma queries that use birthProfile must include: include: { birthProfile: true }

## After every change

Run: cd astro-coach-api && npx tsc --noEmit
Fix all TypeScript errors before committing.
Commit message format: type(scope): description
Types: feat, fix, refactor, chore

---

## Package & environment rules

- ALWAYS use `npx expo install` — NEVER `npm install` for Expo packages.
- ALWAYS use exact version pins — never ^ or ~ in package.json for Expo dependencies.
- ALWAYS run `npx expo-doctor` before every EAS Build submission.
- NEVER mix yarn and npm. Use npm only, always.
- NEVER use react-native-config — use Expo's EXPO_PUBLIC_ prefix for public env vars.
- NEVER use deprecated packages: expo-permissions, expo-app-loading.
- ALWAYS use SafeAreaView from react-native-safe-area-context, NOT from react-native.
- ALWAYS use expo-image, NEVER React Native's Image component.
- ALWAYS use expo-secure-store for sensitive data, NEVER AsyncStorage.
- Before installing any package, verify it is compatible with the current Expo SDK.

---

## TypeScript & code quality

- ALWAYS use TypeScript strict mode — tsconfig: strict: true.
- ALWAYS use functional components with hooks — NEVER class components.
- ALWAYS use arrow function syntax: const MyComponent: React.FC<Props> = () => {}
- ALWAYS use Zod schemas for validating API responses and form inputs.
- ALWAYS use async/await — NEVER raw .then()/.catch() chains.
- ALWAYS use optional chaining (?.) and nullish coalescing (??).
- ALWAYS add JSDoc comments to exported functions.
- NEVER put business logic inside React components — extract to hooks or services.
- NEVER make fetch/axios calls directly from components — use lib/api.ts.
- ALWAYS use path aliases: '@/components/Button' not '../../../components/Button'.
- Naming: PascalCase for components/types, camelCase for functions/vars, UPPER_SNAKE for constants.
- Every time you apply a rule, EXPLICITLY STATE which rule you are following.
- Explain what you are about to do in 1-3 plain English sentences BEFORE writing code.
- Explain WHY you are making every change, not just what it is.

---

## Mobile UI rules

- This is a MOBILE FIRST app — design for small screens first.
- ALWAYS use NativeWind v4 utility classes for styling — no inline StyleSheet unless unavoidable.
- ALWAYS wrap screens in SafeAreaView from react-native-safe-area-context.
- ALWAYS use FlatList or FlashList for lists — NEVER ScrollView with .map() for long lists.
- ALWAYS use KeyboardAvoidingView for screens with text inputs.
- ALWAYS use expo-haptics for touch feedback on interactive elements.
- NEVER use fixed pixel dimensions — use Dimensions API or percentage-based layouts.
- Minimum touch target: 44x44 points (Apple HIG requirement).
- Support system dark mode using NativeWind dark: variants.

---

## RevenueCat & subscriptions

- RevenueCat does NOT work in Expo Go — ALWAYS use EAS development builds for IAP testing.
- ALWAYS call Purchases.configure() in root _layout.tsx before any RevenueCat method.
- ALWAYS call Purchases.logIn(firebaseUid) after auth to link customer to user.
- NEVER hardcode RevenueCat API keys — use EXPO_PUBLIC_REVENUECAT_IOS_KEY + _ANDROID_KEY.
- Bundle identifier (iOS) and package name (Android) MUST match exactly across:
  app.json, App Store Connect, Google Play Console, and RevenueCat dashboard.
- ALWAYS handle all PaywallResult cases: NOT_PRESENTED, ERROR, CANCELLED, PURCHASED, RESTORED.
- ALWAYS verify entitlements server-side before serving premium content — never trust client only.
- NEVER use Stripe or external payment for digital goods in the iOS app (Apple rule).
- ALWAYS include a "Restore Purchases" button in Settings — App Store requirement.
- ALWAYS show subscription terms (price, duration, auto-renewal, cancel info) on paywall.

---

## Privacy (PIPEDA — Canadian users)

- ALWAYS collect explicit consent before storing birth data, with a timestamp.
- ALWAYS provide in-app account deletion that removes all data within 30 days.
- ALWAYS provide data export returning all user data in machine-readable format.
- ALWAYS encrypt sensitive data (journal entries, coaching notes) at rest.
- ALWAYS maintain a consent_records table tracking what the user agreed to and when.
- Store birth_profiles in a separate table from users for data isolation.

---

## Golden rule

When in doubt, choose the safer, simpler, more explicit option.
Protect the founder from mistakes they cannot see.
Always cite which rule from this file you are applying.
